#compdef ogmigo
# ============================================================================
# ogmigo - Go client for ogmios (Cardano blockchain
#           bridge); ChainSync subscriber
#           (Go, Apache-2.0)
#
# Author : Matt Ho (savaki)
# Upstream: https://github.com/savaki/ogmigo
#
# `ogmigo` is the CLI front-end to the savaki/ogmigo
# Go client library for ogmios - the Cardano node-to-
# JSON-WSP bridge that exposes the Ouroboros mini-
# protocols (ChainSync, StateQuery, TxSubmission) over
# a WebSocket / JSON-WSP interface. The binary acts as
# a ChainSync subscriber: it connects to an ogmios
# WebSocket endpoint, walks the Cardano chain from the
# specified starting point, and prints per-block
# (slot, hash, block_no) tuples every `--tick` slots.
#
# Usage:
#   ogmigo [--ogmios WS_URL] [-p SLOT/HASH...]
#          [--tick N]
#
# Flags (urfave/cli/v2):
#   --ogmios <url>          - ogmios WebSocket endpoint
#                              (default
#                              ws://3.21.245.207:1337,
#                              env: OGMIOS)
#   -p, --point <SLOT/HASH> - starting point as
#                              `{slot}/{hash}`
#                              (repeatable, env: POINT)
#   --tick <N>              - display progress every N
#                              slots (default 5000,
#                              env: TICK)
#   -h, --help              - print help
#   -v, --version           - print version
#
# Environment:
#   OGMIOS                  - default --ogmios value
#   POINT                   - default --point value
#   TICK                    - default --tick value
#
# Cardano on-chain data (transactions, blocks, witness
# sets, metadata, governance objects) is CBOR-encoded
# per the Cardano Improvement Proposal CIP-21 spec.
# Every byte that gets hashed for inclusion in a Cardano
# block is canonically-encoded CBOR. The ogmios bridge
# JSON-encodes the chain data for the WebSocket
# transport, but Cardano-specific deserializers
# (transaction body parsing, witness set parsing, plutus
# datum/redeemer decoding) need to round-trip back
# through CBOR for downstream applications.
#
# The fxamacker/cbor lane is built on `github.com/
# fxamacker/cbor/v2 v2.4.0` (declared at upstream go.mod
# HEAD as a direct dep, imported from ouroboros/
# chainsync/types.go for CBOR encoding/decoding of
# Cardano chain data structures), the canonical Go CBOR
# library by Faye Amacker - github.com/fxamacker/cbor,
# 700+ stars. The library is the de-facto Go CBOR
# implementation, FIPS-grade audited (NCC Group +
# Trail of Bits audits), and used by:
#   - Kubernetes (CRD validation via CBOR-encoded schemas
#     since k8s 1.30)
#   - sigstore (bundle parsing + transparency log
#     verification)
#   - IPFS / IPLD (CBOR codec for content-addressed
#     graphs)
#   - go-cose (COSE / CWT signing + encryption, RFC 9052)
#   - OpenSSF Scorecard (sigstore bundle parsing)
#   - Cardano blockchain Go clients (gouroboros, ogmigo,
#     bursa, ...)
#
# fxamacker/cbor implements RFC 8949 end-to-end + the
# canonical/deterministic CBOR (dCBOR) subset used by
# COSE for signing. The library exposes a `cbor.Marshal`
# / `cbor.Unmarshal` API mirroring encoding/json's tag
# convention (`cbor:"key"`), letting Go users drop CBOR
# into existing JSON-tagged structs with no surgery.
#
# ogmigo uses fxamacker/cbor in `ouroboros/chainsync/
# types.go` to round-trip Cardano-specific structures
# (transaction bodies, witness sets, metadata blobs)
# between the on-wire CBOR representation and Go structs
# - this is needed when downstream apps want to operate
# on transaction-level Cardano data rather than just the
# coarse chain-event stream that the CLI's --tick output
# prints.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 247 :: CBOR / RFC 8949 Concise Binary Object
#              Representation
# Round 1440 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 247
#                                  (round-number landmark)
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : enarx/ciborium             [R1439 _mgd]
#   Go      : fxamacker/cbor             [R1440 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : kriszyp/cbor-x             [R1441 closing]
#
# fxamacker/cbor is structurally interesting in this
# axis because of its *FIPS-grade-audited adoption* path.
# Faye Amacker started the library in 2019 to fill the
# gap left by go-codec's broad-but-shallow CBOR support
# - go-codec covers many formats (MsgPack, BSON, JSON,
# CBOR) but didn't track RFC 8949's later updates
# closely. Amacker focused fxamacker/cbor specifically
# on CBOR with these decisions:
#   - tracks RFC 8949 + the canonical CBOR / dCBOR
#     subsets used by COSE + CWT
#   - prioritizes audit-readiness: NCC Group +
#     Trail of Bits independent security audits
#   - tagged-mode + untagged-mode + canonical-mode
#     encoders so apps with different determinism
#     requirements (blockchain canonicality vs IPLD
#     graph canonicality vs COSE) can opt into the
#     right mode
#
# The audit + canonical-mode focus paid off when
# Kubernetes started using CBOR for CRD-schema-aware
# validation (k8s 1.30, 2024); the broader sigstore /
# OpenSSF / cncf supply-chain security ecosystem
# adopted fxamacker/cbor as the canonical Go CBOR lib
# for COSE signature bundles + transparency log
# witnesses.
#
# Structural commentary on the cross-language canonicals:
#   - enarx/ciborium (Rust): chosen after serde_cbor
#     went unmaintained in 2021; rust-lang nursery +
#     Enarx workgroup coordinated migration
#   - fxamacker/cbor (Go): FIPS-grade-audited; adopted
#     by Kubernetes (CRD validation), sigstore (bundle
#     parsing), Cardano (chain data)
#   - kriszyp/cbor-x (Node): high-performance Node CBOR
#     by Kris Zyp (LMDB-js author); schema-aware fast
#     path with plain RFC 8949 fallback
#
# Cross-language interop at the wire format level - same
# RFC 8949 byte string round-trips byte-identically
# through ciborium + fxamacker/cbor + cbor-x. RFC 8949
# Appendix A test vectors validate cross-library
# byte-equivalence.
# ============================================================================

_ogmigo() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '--ogmios[ogmios WebSocket endpoint (env: OGMIOS)]:url:' \
        '*'{-p,--point}'[starting point SLOT/HASH (repeatable, env: POINT)]:point:' \
        '--tick[display progress every N slots (env: TICK)]:N:' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-v,--version}'[print version]'
}

_ogmigo "$@"
